                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="114074" author="rhenwood" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 20:06:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could close this item as &quot;won&apos;t fix&quot; but I am uncertain that is the right approach. I think updating the manual mkfs.lustre command information to say how to use it with ZFS is a valuable exercise, not currently covered by existing resources.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: I have two useful links for ZFS and Lustre:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.lustre.org/Category:ZFS&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.lustre.org/Category:ZFS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://zfsonlinux.org/lustre.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://zfsonlinux.org/lustre.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="113527" author="mdiep" created="Mon, 27 Apr 2015 18:02:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Richard,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you see if this can be closed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64798" author="adilger" created="Wed, 21 Aug 2013 22:41:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems that both this ticket and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-56&quot; title=&quot;Add ZFS setup and formatting information&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-56&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-56&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; were missed for the Lustre 2.4.0 release - the Lustre manual currently has no information at all on how to configure a ZFS filesystem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
